 @{b}Super Nova [#2]@{ub} (1996)

 Stanley and Zev begin a search for Kai's home planet, to discover if there is
 a way for Kai to live without protoblood. When they find it, they discover the
 Poet Man, an image of a long dead man with a hidden agenda. Giggerota, working
 for His Divine Shadow, returns and kidnaps Stanley and then deactivates the
 stabilizers that are keeping the Brunnis sun from going super nova, therefore
 ending the prophecy that states that the last of the Brunnen-G, Kai, will
 destroy His Divine Shadow.

